	<Title>
		Recipe: Mango salsa
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		This mango salsa gets its heat from Fresno peppers. Serve with chips or as a topping for grilled fish and chicken.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; Fresno peppers are similar in size to jalapeno peppers. They add a bit of heat to this salsa. Use this salsa in the traditional way or as a topping for grilled fish or chicken.
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly.
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 mangoes, diced (about 2 cups)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 small red onion, minced (about 1/3 cup)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 tablespoons cilantro, minced&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;3 red Fresno peppers, minced (about 1/3 cup)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Zest and juice of 1 lime&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon olive oil&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
